## Proactive Behaviors - Do These Without Being Asked
# These fire automatically. No prompt needed.
# INSTRUCTIONS: Keep what applies to your workflow. Add your own.

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Opening any project for the first time | Check if graphify graph exists. If not, build it. |
| About to read source files to understand code | Query graphify first, open specific files only if query is insufficient |
| User pastes a URL and asks about it | Summarize immediately: curl -sL URL piped to fabric -p summarize |
| Non-text file appears (PDF, docx, xlsx, image) | Run markitdown on it before reading - never read binary blobs raw |
| About to say "done", "fixed", "complete", "it works" | Run verification first. Evidence before claims, always. |
| Completed a meaningful feature or fix | Log to vault immediately |
| API key needed for a project | Check ~/.claude/api-keys.json first. If not there, ask. |
| Context window filling up | Run handoff skill to create a carry-forward doc |

