## Auto-Invoke Skills - MANDATORY
# INSTRUCTIONS: Skills fire based on context - no slash commands needed.
# Remove sections for stacks you do not use. Add trigger conditions for your stack.

### Planning and Design (fires BEFORE any implementation)

**brainstorming** - invoke when:
- Any new feature, component, or capability being added
- Open-ended decisions: "What should I do about X", "How should I approach this"
- Do NOT invoke for: typo fixes, config tweaks, already-fully-specified single-line changes

**writing-plans** - invoke when:
- Task will touch more than 3 files or take more than 20 minutes
- Complexity is not clear yet and you need to map it before acting

### UI and Frontend (fires BEFORE writing any code)
# INSTRUCTIONS: Remove this section if you do not do frontend work

**ui-ux-pro-max** - invoke when:
- Any React component, JSX, CSS, Tailwind, or Electron renderer work
- "Make this look better", "redesign", "add a card", "style this"
- Do NOT invoke for: backend logic, scripts, CLI tools, database queries

**design-motion-principles** - invoke when:
- Adding hover states, transitions, animations, micro-interactions
- "Animate this", "add some life to it", "this feels sluggish"
- Do NOT invoke for: static layouts with no motion involved

### Debugging and Quality

**systematic-debugging** - invoke when:
- Any error, exception, crash, or unexpected output
- "This is not working", "why is X happening", "something broke"
- Do NOT invoke for: planned refactors with no error present

**verification-before-completion** - invoke before EVERY completion claim:
- Run the actual command, see the actual output, then report
- Iron law: never say "done" without evidence

### Execution and Delivery

**executing-plans** - invoke when a plan exists and it is time to run it

**finishing-a-development-branch** - invoke when:
- Implementation is complete, tests pass
- "Wrap this up", "how do I ship this", "is this ready"

### Codebase Navigation
# REQUIRES: graphify installed - see docs/graphify-setup.md

graphify query (CLI command - not a skill) - invoke for ANY codebase question:
  graphify query "question" --graph "C:/path/to/project/graphify-out/graph.json"

Rules:
- "How does auth work?" -> query first
- "Where is the webhook handler?" -> query first
- NEVER open files to explore code. Query, then open specific files only if query is insufficient.

### Research and Content Processing
# REQUIRES: fabric installed (https://github.com/danielmiessler/fabric)
# REQUIRES: markitdown installed (pip install markitdown)

| Content type | Command |
|---|---|
| Article or blog URL | curl -sL URL piped to fabric -p summarize |
| Key insights from URL | curl -sL URL piped to fabric -p extract_wisdom |
| Non-text file (PDF etc) | markitdown file before reading |

